<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-04-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-04-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="353" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d353">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/4053</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Guatemalan Minister</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MDJ1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Méndez</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-20">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 20, 1917</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received April 25.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: I have the honor
                                to inform you that the President of Guatemala has requested me to
                                convey to you his deepest gratitude and to beg that you will be good
                                enough to repeat these expressions to His Excellency President
                                    <persName corresp="#p_WW1">Wilson</persName>, for the statements
                                which I had the honor to make to him on the part of the Department
                                of State, that the American Government is disposed to assist the
                                Government of Guatemala in the attitude which it has assumed in the
                                state of war which exists between the United States and the Imperial
                                German Government.</p>
                            <p>The President of Guatemala, who is desirious of continuing his
                                support of the principles proclaimed by the United States of
                                America, accepts with the greatest pleasure the assistance offered
                                in a manner as friendly as it is effective, by the illustrious
                                American Government.</p>
                            <p>I avail myself [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_MDJ1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Joaquín Méndez</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>